18/04/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A bomb blast in Pristina late on Sunday (17 April) damaged the offices of a small opposition party.
A UN police spokesman said an organisation called ORA, headed by the prominent Kosovo Albanian publisher Veton Surroi, was the target of the attack.
Three children living in an apartment on the second floor of the building were treated for minor injuries.
In other news, former Prime Minister Ramush Haradinaj returned briefly to Kosovo to attend his brother's funeral on Sunday.
Enver Haradinaj, 23, was killed on Friday in what UN police described as violence between rival clans.
Ramush Haradinaj is facing war crimes charges at the UN tribunal in The Hague.
(Reuters, AP, Beta, Tanjug - 18/04/05;
Reuters - 17/04/05)
